<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#303070" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post114152"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>Lejina Bloodbath</b></font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >325 sustained dps naked!</font><br>
	<p>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Registered: Mar 2002<br>
<!--	Location: <br>
	Posts: 1356-->
</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#303070" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ><img src="images/icons/icon1.gif" border="0" alt=""> <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >When a mob tries to hit you, several things can happen:<br />
<br />
1- He fails his connection check.<br />
Soandso tries to HIT YOU, but miss!<br />
<br />
2- He is successful in his connection check. You are successful in your Dodge check.<br />
Soandso tries to HIT YOU, but you dodge!<br />
<br />
3- He is successful in his connection check. You are successful in your Parry check.<br />
Soandso tries to HIT YOU, but you Parry!<br />
<br />
4- He is successful in his connection check. You are successful in your Riposte check.<br />
Soandso tries to HIT YOU, but you Riposte!<br />
<br />
5- He is successful in his connection check. You fail all your dodge/parry/ripose checks.<br />
Soandso HIT YOU FOR xxx DAMAGE!<br />
<br />
<br />
The Combat Agility will increase the failure of the mobs in 1. It does not increase the occurence of dodge/parry/riposte (2-3-4).<br />
<br />
<br />
When a mob hits you, it can hit you for various amounts of damage. With Combat Stability trained, the mob will hit you, on average, for less. If a mob hit you on average for 200, and you train Combat Stability 3 (10% increase in your mitigation power), then on average this mob will now hit you for 180.<br />
<br />
<br />
Given how the damage repartition is done (20 different value for the damage, and peak of damage at max and minimum), the CS and CA do not give exacly what they should be (CS3 is closer to 9% damage mitigation since max and min damage are not mitigated, and CA3 is more around 9% avoidance since dodge/parry/riposte are not affected by CA), but the above said descriptions of these abilities are accurate enough to give a good idea how they work.</font></p>
	
	<p><p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >__________________<br>
