<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" bgcolor="#000000"  width="100%" align="center"><tr><td>
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#303070" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post114168"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>Lejina Bloodbath</b></font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >325 sustained dps naked!</font><br>
	<p>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Registered: Mar 2002<br>
<!--	Location: <br>
	Posts: 1356-->
</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#303070" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ><img src="images/icons/icon1.gif" border="0" alt=""> <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >In practice, they both lower the damage you take by roughly the same value.<br />
<br />
The differences:<br />
<br />
With CA, you get hit less, so you get stunned less. Easier time to cast your nukes, fd and overall hold agro.<br />
<br />
With CS, the damage you take is less "speaky", you take a more continuous amount of damage and your hp bar drop in a regular scheme, making the job for your healer easier and more predictable.<br />
<br />
Pick whichever that makes you feel its the best, overall the equal eachotcher and in the end you need em both anyway.</font></p>
	
